  "response": "As of 2016, here's a comparison of the Canon 1200D and 1300D:\n\nCanon 1200D:\n- Released in 2014\n- 18MP sensor\n- Basic entry-level DSLR\n- Slightly older technology\n- Less advanced autofocus system\n- Lower performance in low light\n\nCanon 1300D (Rebel T6):\n- Released in 2016\n- 18MP sensor (similar resolution)\n- Improved processor\n- Better low-light performance\n- Upgraded autofocus system\n- Built-in WiFi and NFC\n- Slightly better overall performance\n\nRecommendation for 2016:\n- If budget allows, go for the 1300D\n- Better features and newer technology\n- More future-proof\n- Slightly improved image quality\n- Wireless connectivity\n\nHowever, if the 1200D is significantly cheaper and fits your budget, it's still a good entry-level camera for beginners learning photography basics.\n\nAdditional advice:\n- Consider used/refurbished options\n- Look at lens options\n- Your skills matter more than camera specs\n- Invest in good lenses",
